        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 8:37AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 837 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
southeast of Chloeta, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Gentry...                         Maysville...
Jay...                            Fairmount...
Kansas...                         Lake Eucha State Park...
Gravette...                       Decatur...
Colcord...                        Springtown...
Gallitin...                       Cherokee City...
Siloam Springs...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
